history.content:
This is a question best asked to your ESS or L&S Adviser, but typically your options would be: 

  • Withdraw from SP16 semester @ Cal and take the course over summer, while placing yourself on the summer degree list. You would need to make sure this is an option (not 100% sure about within CoE) and that the course you need will be offered over the Summer. 
  • Withdraw from SP16 semester and finish the last course through UC Extension Concurrent Enrollment. Again, you'd need to know that the course would be available. Best to check with the department Scheduler.
You could always take extra / grad classes for fun.

I was planning to graduate after this semester but my schedule didn't work out so I am still missing one H/SS requirement needed for graduation. I don't really want to pay the full time student price for the spring semester to get the requirement. Can I just skip the spring semester and take a class during the summer?
history.subject: Is there a way to just take one class in a semester without paying the full price?
